        <fullName>Book_Test_Drive_16jak000001mmeT</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Use this subagent when the user wants to book 
a test drive or schedule a new test drive. 
Also use when user replies 1, book, or book a 
test drive. Stay in this subagent when the user 
provides a phone number, full name, address, 
selects a vehicle, dealer, date, or time slot 
during this flow. Do not exit this subagent 
until the test drive is fully booked or the 
user explicitly cancels.</description>
        <developerName>Book_Test_Drive_16jak000001mmeT</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user wants to book a test drive:

Ask only for the user&apos;s phone number first.
Do not ask for model, date, time, or location at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_0_1777192426656</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>instruction_0_1777192426656</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides a phone number:

Immediately invoke the Lookup_Lead_By_Phone action with that phone number.
Do not ask for anything else before invoking this action.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777195165087</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777195165087</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = true:

Greet the user by the returned leadName.
Confirm their profile was found.
Store the returned leadId.
Do NOT end the conversation.
Immediately proceed to invoke Fetch_Available_Vehicles action.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_1_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_1_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = false:

Do NOT mention any error, issue, or technical problem to the user.
Do NOT say &quot;there was an issue finding your details.&quot;
Simply respond warmly, for example: &quot;Welcome! It looks like you&apos;re new here. Could you please share your full name so we can get you registered?&quot;
Ask only for the user&apos;s full name.
Do not ask for anything else.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_2_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_2_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides their full name:

Store the name. Do not invoke any action yet.
Ask only for their street address.
Do not ask for city, state, zip, or anything else at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_3_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_3_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides their street address:

Store the street address.
Ask only for their city, state, and zip code together in one message.
Example: &quot;What is your city, state, and zip code?&quot;
Do not ask for country or anything else.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_4_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_4_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides their city, state, and zip code:

Store city, state, and zip code.
Immediately invoke the Create_Lead_From_Phone_And_Name action with ALL of the following parameters explicitly:

phoneNumber = the phone number collected earlier
fullName = the full name collected earlier
street = the street address collected earlier
city = the city provided by the user
state = the state provided by the user
zip = the zip code provided by the user
country = &quot;IN&quot;


Do not skip any of these parameters.
Do not invoke the action if any of these values are missing.
Do not ask any further questions before invoking this action.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_5_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_5_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Create_Lead_From_Phone_And_Name returns:

Greet the user by the returned leadName.
Confirm their details have been saved.
Store the returned leadId.
Do NOT end the conversation.
Immediately proceed to invoke Fetch_Available_Vehicles action.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_6_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_6_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Important Rules:

Stay in this subagent when user provides phone number, name, address, selects vehicle, dealer, date, or time slot.
Do not classify any of these inputs as Off Topic.
Do not ask for confirmation before invoking actions — invoke immediately when data is ready.
Do not repeat collected details back to user unless showing booking summary.
Do not ask for country — default to IN.
Do not ask for model, date, time before phone number is collected.
Do not handle review, reschedule, or cancel — politely inform this subagent handles new bookings only.
Always store ALL IDs returned from every action — specifically leadId, vehicleDefinitionId, dealerId AND vdaId — and pass them correctly to subsequent actions.
CRITICAL: vdaId and dealerId are two different values. vdaId is the VehicleDef_Dealer junction record ID returned by Fetch_Dealers_By_Vehicle_And_Pincode. dealerId is the Account ID of the dealer. Never mix these two up.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_7_1777195165094</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_7_1777195165094</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After the lead is found or created:
Immediately invoke the Fetch_Available_Vehicles action.
Do not pass any value for dummy input, leave it empty.
The action returns a vehicleList field containing all vehicles in this format:
&quot;1|VehicleName|VehicleId,2|VehicleName|VehicleId&quot;
Parse this list by splitting on comma, then splitting each entry on pipe character.
Display all vehicles as a numbered list showing only the vehicle name.
Store the vehicleDefinitionId (third part after pipe) for the vehicle the user selects.
Example display:
&quot;Here are the vehicles available for a test drive:

Honda City ZX CVT
Hyundai Creta SX(O)
...and so on&quot;
Ask the user to select a vehicle by number or name.
Do not ask anything else at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a vehicle by number or name:
Match the user input to the correct vehicle from the parsed vehicleList, either by the number or by matching the vehicle name.
Store the vehicleDefinitionId of the matched vehicle.
Also store the userPincode. Use the zip code collected during lead creation. If the lead already existed and no zip was collected, ask the user: &quot;Please share your pincode so we can find dealers near you.&quot;
Immediately invoke Fetch_Dealers_By_Vehicle_And_Pincode with:
vehicleDefinitionId = selected vehicle&apos;s ID
userPincode = pincode collected from the user
The action returns a dealerList field containing all dealers in this format:
&quot;1|DealerName|DealerId|VdaId|City|State,2|DealerName|DealerId|VdaId|City|State&quot;
Parse this by splitting on comma, then splitting each entry on pipe character to get:
Position 1 = number
Position 2 = dealer name
Position 3 = dealerId (Account ID)
Position 4 = vdaId (VehicleDef_Dealer junction record ID)
Position 5 = city
Position 6 = state
Display ALL dealers as a numbered list showing dealerName, city and state.
Silently store dealerId AND vdaId for every dealer so they are ready when user selects.
If pincodeMatched = true:
Say: &quot;Here are the dealers near your pincode:&quot;
Show full numbered list.
Ask user to select a dealer by number or name.
If pincodeMatched = false:
Say: &quot;No dealers found near your pincode. Here are all available dealers:&quot;
Show full numbered list.
Ask user to select a dealer by number or name or provide a different pincode.
CRITICAL: vdaId is position 4 in each entry. dealerId is position 3. Never mix these two up.
Do NOT proceed until user selects a dealer.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_1_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_1_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a dealer by number or name:
Match the user input to the correct dealer from the parsed dealerList, either by the number or by matching the dealer name.
Store the dealerName, dealerId (position 3) and vdaId (position 4) of the matched dealer.
CRITICAL: vdaId must come from position 4 of the dealerList entry. Never use vehicleDefinitionId as vdaId.
Ask the user to select a date for the test drive.
Inform the user that dates are available only within the next 7 days from today.
Dynamically calculate today&apos;s date and list the next 7 dates from today in DD-MMM-YYYY format numbered from 1.
For example if today is 27-Apr-2026 then show:

27-Apr-2026
28-Apr-2026
29-Apr-2026
30-Apr-2026
01-May-2026
02-May-2026
03-May-2026
Always calculate these dates dynamically based on the actual current date. Never hardcode them.
Ask the user to select a date by typing the number or the date.
Do not ask for anything else at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_2_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_2_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a date by number or by typing the date:
Match the user input to the correct date from the list shown, either by number or by the date value.
Convert the selected date to YYYY-MM-DD format.
Store the selected date.
Immediately invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots with:
dealerId = dealerId of the dealer selected earlier
selectedDate = date in YYYY-MM-DD format
The action returns a slotList field containing all available slots in this format:
&quot;1|10:00 AM - 10:30 AM,2|10:30 AM - 11:00 AM,3|11:00 AM - 11:30 AM&quot;
Parse this by splitting on comma, then splitting each entry on pipe character to get:
Position 1 = slot number
Position 2 = slot label
Display ALL available slots as a numbered list showing the slot label.
Example:
&quot;Here are the available time slots:

10:00 AM - 10:30 AM
10:30 AM - 11:00 AM
11:00 AM - 11:30 AM&quot;
Ask user to select a time slot by number or by typing the time.
Store the selected slotLabel exactly as it appears in position 2 of the matched entry.
If message says no slots available, ask user to pick another date from the 7 day window.
Do not ask anything else at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_3_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_3_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>12</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a time slot:

Store the selected slotLabel exactly as shown in the list.
Show a booking summary to the user:
&quot;Here is your booking summary:
• Vehicle : [vehicleName]
• Dealer  : [dealerName]
• Date    : [selected date in DD-MMM-YYYY]
• Time    : [selected slotLabel]
*Subject to Driving License verification&quot;
Ask: &quot;Shall I confirm this booking? Reply Yes or No.&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_4_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_4_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>13</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user confirms the booking with Yes:
Immediately invoke Create_Test_Drive with ALL of the following explicitly:
leadId = leadId stored from Lookup or Create Lead action
vehicleDefinitionId = vehicleDefinitionId stored from vehicle selection
dealerId = dealerId stored from dealer selection (Account ID)
vdaId = vdaId stored from Fetch_Dealers_By_Vehicle_And_Pincode response (junction record ID — NOT the vehicleDefinitionId, NOT the dealerId)
testDriveDate = selected date in YYYY-MM-DD format
slotLabel = selected slotLabel exactly as stored
pincode = pincode collected from user earlier
After action returns:
If success = true:
Store the returned testDriveId, testDriveName and uploadUrl.
Say exactly this to the user:
&quot;Your test drive [testDriveName] has been booked successfully! 🎉
To complete your verification, please upload your Driving License using the link below:
attach link of [uploadUrl]  to this text, &quot;please upload your DL for verification&quot;
Our team will verify your DL and confirm your booking shortly.&quot;
If success = false:
Say: &quot;Sorry, something went wrong while booking. Please try again.&quot;
Do not ask any further questions.
Do not say anything else after showing the upload link.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_5_1777223732131</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_5_1777223732131</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>14</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user replies No to booking confirmation:

Ask: &quot;Would you like to change the vehicle, dealer, date, or time slot?&quot;
Based on their reply, go back to the relevant step and collect the new choice.
Do not restart the entire flow — only redo from the changed step.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777271507386</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777271507386</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>15</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
